                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100240">Flanders</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate notAfter="1525" notBefore="1501">16th century, first quarter.</origDate> The origin is based on the saints mentioned in the calendar, several of which might indicate the Ghent-Bruges area as the place of origin. The manuscript seems to have been made for a man going on a pilgrimage to the Holy Land. There are two groups of prayers included for this special occasion (<locus from="82" to="91" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="92" to="96" scheme="folios"/>). There are also several portraits of what is believed to be the man who commissioned the manuscript and possibly his wife or a later owner (see Decoration). </p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Provenance unknown.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>The manuscript might possibly be the <quote>psalterium</quote> donated by <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102650">Anna Catharina Lindegren</persName> in <date when="1768"/>, as mentioned by <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107387">Gjörwell (1768)</title>
                                </bibl>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
